---

Resonant Signal Stability Analysis

A comprehensive stability analysis tool for resonant signals, integrating perturbation response, recurrence quantification, and coupled oscillator dynamics.

🔍 Overview

This tool analyzes synthetic resonant signals to evaluate:

1. Perturbation Stability – How signals respond to increasing noise levels.


2. Recurrence Analysis – Detects periodic structures and predictability.


3. Coupling Synchronization – Examines how signals interact when coupled with external forces.



The framework is designed for scientific research, chaos theory exploration, and AI-driven stability predictions. 🧠📊


---

🚀 Features

✔ Multi-Level Perturbation Analysis:

Tests stability under varying noise intensities.

Tracks signal coherence and amplitude deviations.


✔ Recurrence Quantification Analysis (RQA):

Identifies recurrence patterns.

Measures determinism, entropy, and predictability.


✔ Adaptive Coupling Simulation:

Simulates real-world oscillator interactions with controlled coupling strengths.

Evaluates phase-locking and energy redistribution.


✔ Dynamic Data Visualization:

Time-series charts for direct signal tracking.

Scatter and line graphs to display phase coherence, recurrence metrics, and synchronization trends.



---

🛠 Installation

1️⃣ Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/Resonant-Signal-Analysis.git
cd Resonant-Signal-Analysis

2️⃣ Install Dependencies

Make sure you have Node.js and npm installed. Then, install the required libraries:

npm install

3️⃣ Run the Application

npm start

The interface will be available at http://localhost:3000/.


---

📊 How It Works

1️⃣ Perturbation Analysis

Adds controlled noise to the signal.

Analyzes phase coherence and amplitude stability.

Identifies breakdown points and recovery trends.


2️⃣ Recurrence Quantification

Detects repeating signal structures.

Calculates recurrence rate, determinism, and entropy.

Measures predictability and periodicity.


3️⃣ Coupling Synchronization

Simulates external force interactions.

Measures phase-locking effects and energy shifts.

Helps understand resonance behavior in dynamic systems.



---

📈 Example Output

> 🎯 Goal: Predict when systems become unstable and how they recover.




